reviews.review_text:
A great show from 1987 This a great show from 1987. The band is tight.They open the show hitting on all cylinders, Hey Pocky Way is awesome. Jack Straw is superb. Row Jimmy is amazing, This is my favorite version Row Jimmy. Jerry's solo is flawless. This is one of Jerry's ultimate best solo's ever. (I know that is a big statement to make but listen carefully to his solo and there are not enough words in the dictionary to describe how great that solo was). I love the pace of the song, not too slow, it doesn't drag.
The rest of the show is classic Brent era.
Good sound quality.
Some rise, Some fall, Some climb Nice rainbow full of sound..Inspired playing in this 87' gem..The Terrapin is haunting..Jerry is in fine form~! Give It A Whirl>Forever Grateful>Forever Dead

Feel Good Music By far the best sounding version of this show,
CRISPY BRENT BOARD..

I'm just imagining being there that night, 
lotsa fun in California..

Thanks gang!

Gem of a show! Inspiration move us brightly! This is a well played inspired high energy show, I wish I had it on disc. This is in my top five favorite shows, there’s something about this show that is just magical and inspiring. I first heard some of it on dead hour back in 1994, I recorded it and just wore the tape out. Every song is played with high energy and inspiration, this my favorite heypockeeway and row jimmy, Jerry’s solos on row jimmy are just masterpieces it’s just beautiful rendition. Do yourself a favor and listen, maybe even pout some head phones on. Enjoy!
